CAPE TOWN - Police detectives in the Eastern Cape have arrested a 37-year-old man in connection with the murder of a teenage girl near Qonce. Police said the suspect was apprehended on Thursday night. The man was believed to have been in a relationship with the minor. He's believed to have fled after the 15-year-old girl's body was dug up in the Qawukeni locality, outside King William's Town. The victim was last seen alive over the weekend. Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.